# compare

Side-by-side single-task comparison — give one task, get two outputs to
compare, with blind + vote + rationale capture. Additive; reuses the
benchmark `Variant`/`make_overlay` machinery and `run_single`.

## Must
- Reuse `benchmarks/maintain_suite/run.py::Variant` + `make_overlay` (import,
  never duplicate) to pin each side's model + prompt + sampling
- Run side A then side B SEQUENTIALLY; two model weight-sets cannot coexist in
  oMLX RAM (~25 GB doubled). Cross-model (mode 3) inserts
  `unload_all_loaded(except_for=[model])` + `thermal_guard` between sides
- Mode 1 (luxe-enhanced vs bare champion) drives the bare side via an
  `os.environ` save/restore context manager (LUXE_TIERED_COMPACT=0, interventions
  off, baseline prompt); env overrides must be restored after each side
- Each side gets its own `run_id` so existing `~/.luxe/runs/<run_id>/` logging
  works unchanged
- A non-determinism disclaimer prints immediately before the vote prompt
  (champion is not byte-deterministic at temp=0; this is qualitative, not a
  controlled benchmark)
- Votes record `{winner, reason?}` to an append-only `votes.jsonl` (best-of-N
  re-votes); a reader powers `/compare review` and `luxe compare review <id>`
  so the file is never write-only

## Must not
- Run the two sides concurrently / hold two model weight-sets resident at once
- Present single-task deltas as statistically meaningful
- Mutate global env without restoring it (mode-1 substrate toggles)

## Owns
- src/luxe/compare/**
